{
    "_comment": "Default keyboard/mouse shortcuts. $Ctrl/$Alt/$Shift are placeholders replaced at load with the platform modifier names (Ctrl/Alt/Shift, or the Command/Option/Shift symbols on macOS). Global bindings work in every view; document/grid bindings are context-specific and override a global binding that uses the same key. Context objects map actions to sorted key lists; user configs may store an action as { keys: [...], primacy: key } when a primary key is selected. Installed to /etc/thumbgrid/default-shortcuts.json (admin-editable) with a copy embedded in the binary as a fallback.",
